# API Conventions — GET Listing Endpoints

## Rule: Always use `parseQueryParams`

Every `GET` listing handler **must** call `parseQueryParams` from `src/utils/query-params.ts`. Never hand-parse `page`, `limit`, `sort`, or `filter` from `event.queryStringParameters`.

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
import { parseQueryParams } from '../../utils/query-params.js';

export const handler = async (event: APIGatewayProxyEvent) => {
  const params = parseQueryParams(event.queryStringParameters);
  const result = await listResources(params);
  return buildResponse(200, true, 'Resources retrieved successfully', result);
};

// ❌ WRONG — never do this
const page = parseInt(event.queryStringParameters?.page ?? '1');
```

---

## Standard Query Parameters

| Param | Type | Default | Constraint | Description |
|-------|------|---------|-----------|-------------|
| `page` | integer | `1` | min 1 | Page number (1-based) |
| `limit` | integer | `250` | 1–250 | Records per page |
| `sort` | string | `createdAt:desc` | `column:asc\|desc` | Sort column and direction |
| `filter` | JSON string | none | URL-encoded JSON | Column filters (AND-combined) |

### Filter format
```
?filter={"columnName":{"operator":"eq","value":false}}
```
Operators: `eq` `ne` `gt` `lt` `gte` `lte` `like`

---

## Service Layer: Column Map + Drizzle Builders

Every listing service must define a `COLUMN_MAP` and use the builders:

```typescript
import { count, desc } from 'drizzle-orm';
import type { ParsedQueryParams, QueryColumnMap } from '../../utils/query-params.js';
import { buildOrderBy, buildWhereClause } from '../../utils/query-params.js';

// Map API-facing camelCase names → Drizzle column references
const COLUMN_MAP: QueryColumnMap = {
  createdAt: myTable.createdAt,
  name:      myTable.name,
};

export async function listResources(params: ParsedQueryParams) {
  const { page, limit, offset, sort, filters } = params;
  const orderBy     = buildOrderBy(sort, COLUMN_MAP) ?? desc(myTable.createdAt);
  const whereClause = buildWhereClause(filters, COLUMN_MAP);

  const [rows, countResult] = await Promise.all([
    db.select().from(myTable).where(whereClause).orderBy(orderBy).limit(limit).offset(offset),
    db.select({ total: count() }).from(myTable).where(whereClause),
  ]);

  const total      = countResult[0]?.total ?? 0;
  const totalPages = Math.ceil(total / limit);

  return {
    resources: rows,
    pagination: { page, limit, total, totalPages, hasNext: page < totalPages, hasPrevious: page > 1 },
  };
}
```

